Following the recent catastrophic explosion that occurred at Ilu Abo, near Akure in Ondo State, the Ministry of Mines and Steel Development (MMSD), has lauded the Inspector General of Police (IGP) Mohammed Adamu for setting up a Joint Investigation Team to probe the issues surrounding the occurrence. The Director General of the Nigerian Geological Survey Agency (NGSA), Dr. Abdulrazaq Garba, who was speaking on behalf of the Minister, Arc. Olamilekan Adegbite, assured the police boss of the fullness of the agency in carrying out the enquiry. However, Engr Garba, in a statement issued, cautioned the scientific community and other relevant institutions to refrain from making public statements on the matter as it is now squarely a police investigation. He also stated that all samples recovered from the site should be turned in to the investigation team to enable a robust understanding of the incident. The Director General assured Nigerians that the findings of the team will be scientific and involve necessary stakeholders for an all encompassing submission to be made. He equally assured that at the end of the investigation, a report presenting the fact concerning  what happened, will be presented for the public’s easy comprehension in order to put the records straight.